children.subject: Because the class is still open so CS majors during adj period are enrolling in the course.

But since it is the adjustment period, why do they still get preference when enrolling into the class? In the adjustment period, all reserved spots/preferences are supposed to be released and the waitlist is supposed to be followed in order. It doesn't make sense that some people would still be able to enroll ahead of a waitlist of 220 people when it should be open to everyone.
And now 2 more spots are gone and my discussion section has filled up suddenly with no change in my waitlist position and no clear explanation to what is happening. This is extremely frustrating :(

history.content: What's going on with the CS 188 waitlist? I kinda assumed that once the adjustment period started today, they'd go through the waitlist in order and enroll people if possible (as according to the advisor's comment in @1860). However as my spot on the waitlist hasn't changed (and enrollment in the class hasn't shot up), it appears this isn't the case. It also seems to be the case though that the last 50 spots (as of the 9:00 am) in the class weren't reserved/not available because there are now only 48 spots left. So what is going on? If the waitlist isn't changing like it's supposed to, where are these new enrollments coming from? When can we expect the waitlist procedure in @1860 to be followed if not at the start of the adjustment period? There is still space in my discussion and I don't have a time conflict so I should get in even if all 130 people in front of me can't. I'm just confused as to when the waitlist will be processed and why I'm being skipped even though it is the adjustment period.
